Lemon Cove first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Lemon Cove had a population of 298. The population density was {{convert|223.2|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Lemon Cove was 209 (70.1%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 5 (1.7%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1 (0.3%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.3%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 29 (9.7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 53 (17.8%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 82 persons (27.5%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Lemon Cove CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0641110 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 24, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 117 households, out of which 49 (41.9%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 80 (68.4%) were married-couple households, 5 (4.3%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 28 (23.9%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 4 (3.4%) had a male householder with no partner present. 13 households (11.1%) were one person, and 9 (7.7%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.55.<ref name=DP1/> There were 102 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (87.2% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Lemon Cove CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0641110 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 24, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 70 people (23.5%) under the age of 18, 13 people (4.4%) aged 18 to 24, 73 people (24.5%) aged 25 to 44, 85 people (28.5%) aged 45 to 64, and 57 people (19.1%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 39.5{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 88.6 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 131 housing units at an average density of {{convert|98.1|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 117 (89.3%) were occupied. Of these, 80 (68.4%) were owner-occupied, and 37 (31.6%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0641110|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715030629/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0641110|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Lemon Cove CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Lemon Cove had a population of 308. The population density was {{convert|369.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Lemon Cove was 261 (84.7%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 5 (1.6%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 3 (1.0%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 2 (0.6%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 12 (3.9%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 25 (8.1%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 76 persons (24.7%).

The Census reported that 308 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 120 households, out of which 39 (32.5%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 53 (44.2%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 19 (15.8%) had a female householder with no husband present, 7 (5.8%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 4 (3.3%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 37 households (30.8%) were made up of individuals, and 10 (8.3%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.57.  There were 79 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (65.8% of all households); the average family size was 3.16.

The population was spread out, with 82 people (26.6%) under the age of 18, 32 people (10.4%) aged 18 to 24, 58 people (18.8%) aged 25 to 44, 92 people (29.9%) aged 45 to 64, and 44 people (14.3%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 39.6 years. For every 100 females, there were 106.7 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 107.3 males.

There were 153 housing units at an average density of {{convert|183.5|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 77 (64.2%) were owner-occupied, and 43 (35.8%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0%; the rental vacancy rate was 6.0%.  202 people (65.6% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 106 people (34.4%) lived in rental housing units.

